1
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:25,775
HEUNG'S KITCHEN, HOUSE OF OHJUK

2
00:00:29,654 --> 00:00:32,365
He's in there. Over there.

3
00:00:33,199 --> 00:00:34,075
Oh, no.

4
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:38,288
There goes the dignity of our clan’s heir.

5
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:40,874
I can't believe how stubborn he is.

6
00:00:40,957 --> 00:00:44,627
Are you trying to kill yourself?
Get up right now!

7
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:49,591
Goodness, Ho-ja. At this rate,
he’ll die before he even gets married.

8
00:00:49,674 --> 00:00:54,471
He's been begging for two days,
barely dressed and refusing to eat.

9
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:56,514
Why not just let him marry--

10
00:00:56,598 --> 00:00:57,432
Quiet!

11
00:00:58,808 --> 00:01:01,686
You called off a wedding
we spent two years planning

12
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:05,106
all for a girl
you've been seeing for two months.

13
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:08,151
And now you dare pull a stunt like this?

14
00:01:08,651 --> 00:01:11,821
If you're going to abandon
your duties and honor like this,

15
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:14,074
you may as well take everything off!

16
00:01:19,913 --> 00:01:22,916
You fool! How dare you?

17
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:31,925
Are you all right?

18
00:01:32,675 --> 00:01:34,552
For God's sake!

19
00:01:34,636 --> 00:01:36,846
You can't take off your underwear!

20
00:01:38,848 --> 00:01:41,184
Why did you come? This is embarrassing.

21
00:01:42,811 --> 00:01:45,313
-Who told <i>her </i>to come?
-I couldn't possibly guess.

22
00:01:45,396 --> 00:01:47,649
Don't just stand there!

23
00:01:47,732 --> 00:01:49,984
Get her out of here right this instant!

24
00:01:53,363 --> 00:01:56,908
-Goodness, they're in big trouble now.
-Give up already.

25
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:00,370
You'll never win against her.

26
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:04,582
I may have never won,

27
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:07,836
but I've never given up first either.

28
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:11,214
So just promise me

29
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,133
that you'll never

30
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:16,594
let go of my hand.

31
00:02:32,152 --> 00:02:34,154
Heung, open your eyes!

32
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:35,905
Heung!

33
00:02:36,489 --> 00:02:38,616
What am I going to do? Heung!

34
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:49,711
That little…

35
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:52,630
Jae-mi is pregnant with my child, Mother!

36
00:02:57,343 --> 00:02:59,554
-She's pregnant?
-What a moron.

37
00:03:10,398 --> 00:03:11,900
<i>What if they find out?</i>

38
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:14,402
<i>That you're not actually pregnant.</i>

39
00:03:15,612 --> 00:03:18,281
<i>How can you be pregnant</i>
<i>when you're in menopause?</i>

40
00:03:18,781 --> 00:03:22,952
<i>Do you want to have</i>
<i>as many babies as possible, boys or girls,</i>

41
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:26,915
<i>and set the Guinness World Record</i>
<i>for having the most children?</i>

42
00:03:27,498 --> 00:03:28,708
<i>I know I can do it.</i>

43
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:32,378
<i>And will he still love you?</i>
<i>Even if you end his bloodline?</i>

44
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:39,862
There you go.

45
00:04:41,572 --> 00:04:43,074
Sir, are you okay?

46
00:04:43,157 --> 00:04:45,660
Can you hear me, sir? What's your name?

47
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:51,958
Forgive me.

48
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:55,628
I…

49
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:01,551
I'm not sure if I can hold onto your hand.

50
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:05,138
I'm sorry.

51
00:05:28,411 --> 00:05:29,954
What did you mean by that?

52
00:05:32,707 --> 00:05:33,916
"You're all mine"?

53
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,710
No. Before that.

54
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,923
-"I'm never letting go of your hand"?
-Before that.

55
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:46,054
"I'll die."

56
00:05:46,137 --> 00:05:47,722
What did you mean by that?

57
00:05:49,223 --> 00:05:53,394
I meant that I'll gladly leave your life
if that makes you happy.

58
00:05:58,066 --> 00:05:58,941
For good?

59
00:06:00,777 --> 00:06:02,278
Yes, for good.

60
00:06:02,862 --> 00:06:03,696
Pinky promise?

61
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:10,703
-Off you go, then.
-Go where?

62
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:12,246
-To hell.
-What?

63
00:06:15,917 --> 00:06:17,168
Damn, that's cold.

64
00:06:18,461 --> 00:06:20,254
-Hey!
-Listen up.

65
00:06:20,338 --> 00:06:22,715
A piece of advice in case you survive.

66
00:06:22,799 --> 00:06:26,302
In the wild, the sneaky cowards win!

67
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:28,429
You got that, you idiot?

68
00:06:30,848 --> 00:06:33,226
Man, she's a real nutjob.

69
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:46,280
Why is my life getting so fun
just as it's about to end?

70
00:06:47,323 --> 00:06:48,783
It's making me want to live.

71
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:02,797
MR. PLANKTON

72
00:07:18,312 --> 00:07:22,024
NAMWON POLICE

73
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:46,424
PAYPHONE

74
00:07:57,518 --> 00:07:58,644
MOTHER

75
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,813
Well, I'm off now.

76
00:08:00,897 --> 00:08:02,899
Wait a minute. Chief. Please, sir.

77
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:04,609
What's the matter now?

78
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:07,653
You said he left his car behind.

79
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:11,199
You might find something
if you run his prints or license number.

80
00:08:11,282 --> 00:08:12,617
I know that.

81
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:15,203
I'll let you know if we have any updates.

82
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:16,871
-Please be patient.
-Please.

83
00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:17,914
-Wait.
-Seriously?

84
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:19,874
-I'm just frustrated.
-Are you now?

85
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:21,584
How do you think I feel then?

86
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:24,712
And where is this person
who's supposed to be picking you up?

87
00:08:25,296 --> 00:08:26,964
-Well, that's--
-Answer it.

88
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:30,718
I'd better get going. See you.

89
00:08:38,809 --> 00:08:42,647
Hi, Mother. I'm sorry. My battery is low.

90
00:08:43,147 --> 00:08:44,982
<i>I can't talk for long anyway.</i>

91
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:46,567
-Good night, sir.
-Jae-mi?

92
00:08:47,485 --> 00:08:49,195
-Jae-mi!
-Jae-mi? It's her?

93
00:08:49,278 --> 00:08:51,447
-It's Jae-mi.
-Jae-mi, where are you?

94
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:54,700
Where are you? Are you okay? Are you hurt?

95
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:58,037
Here, can you track her? Please track her.

96
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,706
Jae-mi, where are you?

97
00:09:01,707 --> 00:09:04,502
<i>I'll come and get you right away.</i>

98
00:09:04,585 --> 00:09:06,003
I'm scared.

99
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,552
It's getting harder to find my way back.

100
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:14,971
<i>Are you locked up?</i>

101
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:16,973
Did that bastard lock you up?

102
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:18,057
No, he didn't.

103
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:21,978
I just feel so hopeless right now.

104
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:25,690
Even if you do find me,

105
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:30,736
I'm too scared to face the consequences.

106
00:09:31,362 --> 00:09:34,574
You won't have to. This isn't your fault.

107
00:09:34,657 --> 00:09:35,992
I lied.

108
00:09:38,911 --> 00:09:42,456
To your mother and all your family.

109
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:45,293
I lied to every one of them.

110
00:09:45,793 --> 00:09:48,504
I'm the one who lied
about you being pregnant.

111
00:09:49,046 --> 00:09:53,384
<i>I'll take care of everything. Don't worry.</i>

112
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:55,970
<i>Just tell me where you are.</i>

113
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,889
<i>I'll come get you. Jae-mi? Are you there?</i>

114
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:00,433
Hang up now.

115
00:10:00,516 --> 00:10:02,018
Did that bastard just--

116
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:04,729
Hello?

117
00:10:05,855 --> 00:10:08,941
No, I lost her! Jae-mi!

118
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:10,151
What on earth?

119
00:10:10,234 --> 00:10:13,195
This is the pay phone right outside.

120
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,989
-Yes, right there.
-Exactly.

121
00:10:15,072 --> 00:10:16,073
Jae-mi!

122
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:20,077
Jae-mi!

123
00:10:21,662 --> 00:10:22,830
Jae-mi.

124
00:10:24,498 --> 00:10:27,293
Jae-mi.

125
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:28,836
Jae-mi!

126
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:31,839
Jae-mi.

127
00:10:33,841 --> 00:10:36,594
I'll kill that bastard
if he lays a finger on her.

128
00:10:36,677 --> 00:10:37,928
Jae-mi!

129
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:40,931
Jae-mi!

130
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:43,559
Jae-mi!

131
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:49,482
They say being cursed at
extends your life.

132
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:53,027
With all the curses I've had spewed at me,

133
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,990
shouldn't I get to live
for, like, a gazillion years?

134
00:11:07,249 --> 00:11:10,086
THREE-WAY JUNCTION NOODLES

135
00:11:17,176 --> 00:11:19,345
Have some. You haven't eaten all day.

136
00:11:24,975 --> 00:11:27,603
That will burn a hole
in your empty stomach.

137
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:30,523
Eat up. It'll go down easier.

138
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,946
Old ladies can really cook, huh?

139
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:39,156
What's that? Did you want more rice?

140
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,034
I said it's delicious. God bless you.

141
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:46,807
What is it?

142
00:12:47,641 --> 00:12:48,726
Your chest.

143
00:12:52,563 --> 00:12:54,398
You got food on your dress there.

144
00:12:58,986 --> 00:13:00,070
Take some wet wipes.

145
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:03,073
When did this happen?

146
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:08,245
I'm glad you're still
the same old Jo Jae-mi.

147
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:15,544
You're still just as high-maintenance,
clumsy, and hot-tempered as I remembered.

148
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:20,674
You may act tough,
but you're too soft to be truly brazen.

149
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:26,222
You really don't know me at all.
You never did.

150
00:13:27,723 --> 00:13:31,435
I've been more than just brazen.

151
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:36,315
I've been as bold as brass.

152
00:13:37,983 --> 00:13:39,527
I guess that brass got rusty.

153
00:13:43,447 --> 00:13:45,449
If you were as bold as you say you are,

154
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:48,285
you wouldn't have hidden earlier.

155
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:50,496
Premature menopause?

156
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:51,914
Who gives a damn?

157
00:13:51,997 --> 00:13:53,624
An important family? Big deal.

158
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:57,211
What's the point
of a long bloodline anyway?

159
00:13:59,713 --> 00:14:00,840
Forget it.

160
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:06,136
If you really were as bold as brass,
you'd have run into his arms and said,

161
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:09,974
"I'm going to live
happily ever after with this man."

162
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:11,809
You said it yourself.

163
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:15,271
Your happiness comes first.

164
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:18,774
So why be such a wuss?

165
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:26,740
Because I don't think I will be happy.

166
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:43,883
I guess marrying
into such a respected family

167
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:48,137
ought to sort out my messed-up life.

168
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:54,351
By taking all that he has to give,
I'd finally feel whole.

169
00:14:55,311 --> 00:14:57,980
If that's happiness, I should enjoy it.

170
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:01,817
But…

171
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:05,487
I might just end up…

172
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,326
taking away

173
00:15:11,452 --> 00:15:12,703
all of his happiness.

174
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:20,836
What if I marry him to be happy

175
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:23,839
yet end up becoming
the source of <i>his </i>misery?

176
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:28,510
I might end up
destroying him and his family.

177
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:32,806
I might end up

178
00:15:33,641 --> 00:15:36,727
burning his family tree to the ground.

179
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:40,773
And the thought terrifies me.

180
00:15:52,159 --> 00:15:56,080
I don't ever want to be
the seed of anyone's misery.

181
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:01,877
"Seed of misery"?

182
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:08,592
Some of us are just born that way.

183
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:10,636
Who?

184
00:16:10,719 --> 00:16:12,972
Just someone. Number 137.

185
00:16:21,355 --> 00:16:22,523
Yes.

186
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:26,944
Thank you for everything
that you've done, Chief.

187
00:16:27,027 --> 00:16:30,114
Of course. You needn't worry about him.

188
00:16:30,197 --> 00:16:32,825
He's usually
very strait-laced and responsible.

189
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:36,704
He'll never get into
this kind of trouble again.

190
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:39,206
You're so wrong about me!

191
00:16:39,289 --> 00:16:42,918
I guess you thought
I was some dumb pushover.

192
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:44,670
-Hey, stop him.
-Bring it on.

193
00:16:44,753 --> 00:16:46,213
Let's do this. Come on!

194
00:16:47,297 --> 00:16:48,841
Please. Have a seat--

195
00:16:48,924 --> 00:16:50,801
Get your hands off me! No!

196
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:55,514
That bastard stole my bride
right out from under me yet again.

197
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:58,308
-I've got nothing to lose now.
-I understand.

198
00:16:58,392 --> 00:17:00,728
No real man
would ever put up with that shit!

199
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:02,146
-Go for it!
-Show them!

200
00:17:02,229 --> 00:17:03,647
You misjudged me!

201
00:17:06,066 --> 00:17:07,818
That's enough already.

202
00:17:07,901 --> 00:17:11,780
This is a family matter.
We will handle it ourselves.

203
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:14,408
We can't keep you
from your official duties.

204
00:17:14,992 --> 00:17:16,869
This is obstruction of justice!

205
00:17:16,952 --> 00:17:21,081
Why don't you talk about justice
once you've actually served it?

206
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:23,751
-For God's sake.
-Heung! Don't let go, man!

207
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:25,419
Keep a tight grip on it!

208
00:17:26,587 --> 00:17:29,798
Just do something.
Put him on some kind of wanted list.

209
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:32,384
Or else I'm not going anywhere.

210
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:34,428
I won't take a single step--

211
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:39,183
Wait, who are… Who are you?

212
00:17:39,683 --> 00:17:42,227
Hey, put me down. Please put me down!

213
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:43,395
Fetch his clothes.

214
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:48,817
Hey, no!

215
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:52,237
That was so badass.

216
00:17:52,738 --> 00:17:54,907
Do you have someone else
you're counting on?

217
00:17:56,658 --> 00:17:59,912
You're going to handle it yourself
without the police?

218
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:06,418
A woman about to join
a prestigious family,

219
00:18:06,919 --> 00:18:08,754
a Korean food dynasty,

220
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:12,674
gets kidnapped by some thug
on her wedding day,

221
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:19,473
and she happens to be with child.

222
00:18:21,141 --> 00:18:22,309
Can you imagine?

223
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:26,522
Journalists would have a field day.

224
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:29,650
They'd probably say
that punk did all kinds of things to…

225
00:18:31,026 --> 00:18:33,320
People will believe anything these days.

226
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:36,740
Nothing good will come from making a fuss.

227
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:40,953
If anything needs
to be buried or disposed of,

228
00:18:41,578 --> 00:18:43,163
I'll do it myself quietly.

229
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,052
Feeling hopeless?

230
00:18:58,929 --> 00:18:59,888
A little.

231
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:06,103
It feels like I've been running
towards the finish line forever.

232
00:19:07,104 --> 00:19:09,398
And just as I get there, it disappears.

233
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:13,986
And I can't stop
because of the momentum built up.

234
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:18,824
I don't know where to go from here.

235
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:22,369
I'm too exhausted.

236
00:19:26,331 --> 00:19:27,499
What should I do?

237
00:19:33,172 --> 00:19:34,214
Want my advice?

238
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:41,013
I know I'll regret listening to it,

239
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:42,431
but go ahead.

240
00:19:44,516 --> 00:19:47,728
Don't set yourself
any destinations in life from now on.

241
00:19:48,437 --> 00:19:51,356
If you lose your way
while running towards something,

242
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:55,152
it sets you adrift, like with you now.

243
00:19:56,069 --> 00:19:59,072
But if you lose your way
while wandering aimlessly,

244
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:01,825
it doesn't set you adrift.

245
00:20:01,909 --> 00:20:03,577
It just makes you a drifter,

246
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:05,245
like me.

247
00:20:07,664 --> 00:20:10,792
So, what do you say?
Want to become a drifter with me?

248
00:20:12,669 --> 00:20:15,672
Do you know what
they call people who talk like you?

249
00:20:16,506 --> 00:20:17,341
What?

250
00:20:19,426 --> 00:20:20,969
Delusional freaks.

251
00:20:21,553 --> 00:20:23,972
I know you agree. Don't pretend you don't.

252
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,349
Where are you going?

253
00:20:25,432 --> 00:20:27,100
Stay there, you delusional freak.

254
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:29,019
Come on, let's be drifters together.

255
00:20:29,102 --> 00:20:30,646
No! Stop following me!

256
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:33,148
-Just for a week!
-Not even for one second!

257
00:20:36,151 --> 00:20:38,403
