508
00:39:47,176 --> 00:39:48,094
How beautiful.

509
00:39:50,304 --> 00:39:52,306
-First time here?
-It's so nice.

510
00:39:56,602 --> 00:39:57,478
This way.

511
00:40:02,566 --> 00:40:04,693
-Oh my God! Damn!
-Hey!

512
00:40:06,445 --> 00:40:07,947
-For God's sake…
-Snake!

513
00:40:08,030 --> 00:40:09,615
-Fuck!
-A snake, shit!

514
00:40:09,698 --> 00:40:11,200
Snake!

515
00:40:11,826 --> 00:40:12,701
Snake!

516
00:40:13,202 --> 00:40:16,122
<i>It was almost impossible</i>
<i>to track down Ko Jae-geun.</i>

517
00:40:16,205 --> 00:40:19,875
<i>He's been jumping</i>
<i>from place to place like a grasshopper.</i>

518
00:40:19,959 --> 00:40:21,710
<i>The most recent info I've got</i>

519
00:40:21,794 --> 00:40:25,798
<i>is that he lives like a hermit,</i>
<i>up on Mount Gudeok, but I'm not sure.</i>

520
00:40:31,804 --> 00:40:32,680
Hello?

521
00:40:35,850 --> 00:40:37,017
Is anyone inside?

522
00:40:37,101 --> 00:40:38,602
No. Where the hell…

523
00:40:40,604 --> 00:40:41,564
Hello?

524
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:48,237
-I'm beat.
-Who are you?

525
00:41:00,207 --> 00:41:01,125
Answer me.

526
00:41:02,001 --> 00:41:06,255
Well… I'm…

527
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:13,345
Sir, do you live here?

528
00:41:14,013 --> 00:41:14,972
Yes. So what?

529
00:41:15,055 --> 00:41:17,975
And your name is Mr. Ko Jae-geun?

530
00:41:24,732 --> 00:41:26,275
Who are you people?

531
00:41:26,358 --> 00:41:28,319
Oh, I'm sorry.

532
00:41:28,402 --> 00:41:30,696
We should've introduced ourselves.

533
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:34,158
Let me quickly explain why we're here.

534
00:41:34,241 --> 00:41:35,493
Well, we're here

535
00:41:36,827 --> 00:41:39,371
looking for the sperm that created him!

536
00:41:46,545 --> 00:41:47,713
Sperm donor.

537
00:41:48,547 --> 00:41:50,799
Right, the sperm donor. Sorry.

538
00:41:51,592 --> 00:41:55,763
He's searching for his biological father

539
00:41:55,846 --> 00:41:58,140
and I'm just accompanying him.

540
00:42:01,685 --> 00:42:02,645
And?

541
00:42:02,728 --> 00:42:06,941
We're not here
to disrupt your life in any way, sir.

542
00:42:07,024 --> 00:42:08,275
There's no need to worry.

543
00:42:08,359 --> 00:42:11,237
He just wants to know
who his biological father is.

544
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:14,281
You know,
the typical identity crisis cliché.

545
00:42:14,365 --> 00:42:18,202
Self-discovery and finding your roots.
"Who am I? Where do I come from?"

546
00:42:18,786 --> 00:42:20,496
That sort of thing.

547
00:42:22,039 --> 00:42:25,042
So, if it's not too much to ask,

548
00:42:25,125 --> 00:42:28,212
we were wondering
if we could get your toothbrush,

549
00:42:28,295 --> 00:42:31,215
some of your hair, or a saliva sample.

550
00:42:50,568 --> 00:42:51,777
Interesting.

551
00:43:00,202 --> 00:43:02,413
Right, Unpung Pharm.

552
00:43:02,496 --> 00:43:06,000
I did donate a few times
when I worked as a sales rep there.

553
00:43:06,083 --> 00:43:10,004
I'd lost a lot on the stock market,
so I was running low on cash.

554
00:43:10,588 --> 00:43:14,758
They gave you a gift card
worth 100,000 won for every donation,

555
00:43:14,842 --> 00:43:16,135
so I went for it.

556
00:43:16,677 --> 00:43:19,597
It was a pretty decent sum at the time.

557
00:43:20,889 --> 00:43:23,100
So you're a tango dancer?

558
00:43:26,145 --> 00:43:27,146
I used to be.

559
00:43:27,855 --> 00:43:30,190
When my dear Ok-jeong passed away,

560
00:43:30,274 --> 00:43:34,194
I couldn't find another partner
I could connect with at that level.

561
00:43:34,278 --> 00:43:35,738
So I quit years ago.

562
00:43:46,332 --> 00:43:49,001
I dabbled a bit
in ballroom dancing myself.

563
00:43:53,255 --> 00:43:54,214
Hey.

564
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:57,343
Hey, you've got some rhythm there.

565
00:43:57,926 --> 00:43:58,969
-Hey.
-Right?

566
00:43:59,470 --> 00:44:00,929
-Of course.
-Let's see.

567
00:44:02,264 --> 00:44:04,558
The tango is all about connection.

568
00:44:05,851 --> 00:44:07,770
Our hearts become one.

569
00:44:07,853 --> 00:44:11,106
One heart and four legs.

570
00:44:12,441 --> 00:44:13,567
That's it.

571
00:44:13,651 --> 00:44:17,029
All right. Hey! Slide. Okay.

572
00:44:19,114 --> 00:44:20,199
Am I any good?

573
00:44:28,415 --> 00:44:30,167
He's a bit of a buzzkill.

574
00:44:37,716 --> 00:44:39,843
You don't live with your family?

575
00:44:39,927 --> 00:44:40,928
I don't have any.

576
00:44:42,721 --> 00:44:45,641
Back in the day,
I had a bit of a bad habit

577
00:44:45,724 --> 00:44:47,309
so my wife and I split up.

578
00:44:47,810 --> 00:44:48,894
We never had kids.

579
00:44:49,395 --> 00:44:51,021
Well, I might have one now.

580
00:44:54,775 --> 00:44:57,778
Apparently, paternity tests
can come back in a day now.

581
00:44:57,861 --> 00:44:59,947
Available 24-7. Amazing, isn't it?

582
00:45:00,030 --> 00:45:01,448
Really that quick?

583
00:45:02,950 --> 00:45:06,745
In that case,
why don't you stay the night?

584
00:45:07,788 --> 00:45:10,708
I want to see the test results too.

585
00:45:10,791 --> 00:45:11,709
Could we?

586
00:45:12,626 --> 00:45:13,460
Thank God.

587
00:45:13,544 --> 00:45:16,463
I was worried
about going back down the mountain.

588
00:45:16,547 --> 00:45:17,673
-Right?
-Yes.

589
00:45:17,756 --> 00:45:19,466
All right, then.

590
00:45:19,550 --> 00:45:23,011
The attic is spacious.
Let me clean it up for you.

591
00:45:23,095 --> 00:45:24,138
Give me a moment.

592
00:45:30,936 --> 00:45:34,356
You two have that same sly smile.

593
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:35,566
It's uncanny.

594
00:45:36,817 --> 00:45:38,527
I can't believe it.

595
00:45:38,610 --> 00:45:39,778
Right? You see it too?

596
00:45:39,862 --> 00:45:43,282
I can't believe
how direct you were with him.

597
00:45:45,367 --> 00:45:46,952
And it worked.

598
00:45:47,828 --> 00:45:50,664
Honesty really is the best policy.

599
00:45:51,832 --> 00:45:53,542
It's called people skills.

600
00:45:53,625 --> 00:45:57,671
You might want to learn from me
instead of always trying to con people.

601
00:45:57,755 --> 00:45:59,673
I don't always try to con people.

602
00:45:59,757 --> 00:46:01,383
Sure you do.

603
00:46:11,101 --> 00:46:12,603
From Namwon to Busan?

604
00:46:13,187 --> 00:46:15,230
What business does he have there

605
00:46:15,314 --> 00:46:18,609
that would make him leave
so early in the morning with Jae-mi?

606
00:46:18,692 --> 00:46:20,527
There must be a good reason.

607
00:46:21,487 --> 00:46:23,614
Where did they go after the station?

608
00:46:26,784 --> 00:46:27,910
You don't know?

609
00:46:29,203 --> 00:46:31,246
Are you unable to talk or refusing?

610
00:46:32,956 --> 00:46:35,709
Or do you just not want to talk to me?

611
00:46:35,793 --> 00:46:37,419
Is that it?

612
00:46:39,129 --> 00:46:42,132
See? That's why you shouldn't eat so fast.
Give me your hand.

613
00:46:43,842 --> 00:46:45,052
Just give it.

614
00:46:46,512 --> 00:46:49,890
See how tense it is?
You're all blocked up. Relax.

615
00:46:50,891 --> 00:46:52,518
So you do understand me. Good.

616
00:46:52,601 --> 00:46:53,685
That's it, great.

617
00:46:54,728 --> 00:46:56,772
We're partners now, right?

618
00:46:56,855 --> 00:46:58,941
We'll have to stick together

619
00:46:59,024 --> 00:47:01,485
until we find that jerk Chae Seung-hyeok.

620
00:47:01,568 --> 00:47:03,862
We need to be able to communicate.

621
00:47:06,156 --> 00:47:07,324
Did you know

622
00:47:08,200 --> 00:47:12,037
people communicate with each other
in three different ways?

623
00:47:13,622 --> 00:47:16,291
One is through words.

624
00:47:17,167 --> 00:47:20,379
As in actually talking.
Another is through eye contact.

625
00:47:21,797 --> 00:47:24,091
And lastly, physical touch.

626
00:47:29,972 --> 00:47:32,182
At least we managed one of those today.

627
00:47:32,975 --> 00:47:34,476
Right?

628
00:47:42,317 --> 00:47:45,779
John? Mr. John Na,
will you give me a hand with these?

629
00:47:46,613 --> 00:47:49,700
He looks all flushed.
He must have awful indigestion.

630
00:48:00,669 --> 00:48:03,297
You forgot these! Come on, open up.

631
00:48:08,635 --> 00:48:09,845
Where am I?

632
00:48:09,928 --> 00:48:11,263
What the hell should I do?

633
00:48:11,346 --> 00:48:13,765
I'm fucking exhausted.

634
00:48:17,060 --> 00:48:19,146
This is killing me.

635
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:26,153
Text me the results

636
00:48:27,905 --> 00:48:29,907
by tomorrow morning at the latest.

637
00:48:29,990 --> 00:48:33,869
Fucking hell. If it wasn't urgent,
you could've just mailed it!

638
00:48:33,952 --> 00:48:36,997
Did you have to make me
climb all the way up here? Damn it.

639
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:39,541
True. Well, bye. Watch out for the snakes.

640
00:48:39,625 --> 00:48:41,168
Wait, snakes? Shit.

641
00:48:43,378 --> 00:48:45,505
There. Now this is a good one.

642
00:48:48,091 --> 00:48:52,220
Living here and eating things like this,
you could easily live past 100.

643
00:48:52,304 --> 00:48:53,263
You never know

644
00:48:53,347 --> 00:48:55,015
what fate has in store.

645
00:48:55,098 --> 00:48:58,936
It's not determined by the land,
but by the heavens above.

646
00:48:59,019 --> 00:49:00,479
Is that so?

647
00:49:00,562 --> 00:49:03,565
Back in my big pharma days,
I had several brain surgeries.

648
00:49:03,649 --> 00:49:05,859
They thought I wouldn't make it.

649
00:49:05,943 --> 00:49:06,860
Oh, really?

650
00:49:06,944 --> 00:49:08,987
So I gave up on everything

651
00:49:09,071 --> 00:49:12,282
and started wandering around aimlessly.

652
00:49:12,366 --> 00:49:15,327
But look at me now.
Still here, doing pretty well.

653
00:49:15,911 --> 00:49:17,746
That's when I realized.

654
00:49:17,829 --> 00:49:19,331
I shouldn't be so desperate.

655
00:49:19,915 --> 00:49:22,292
It's that very desperation

656
00:49:22,376 --> 00:49:24,920
that will take years off your life.

657
00:49:26,129 --> 00:49:27,422
Yes, you're right.

658
00:49:27,506 --> 00:49:28,382
Right?

659
00:49:32,886 --> 00:49:35,472
I hope you are Hae Jo's father.

660
00:49:36,890 --> 00:49:37,808
Why?

661
00:49:37,891 --> 00:49:40,143
I think you guys will hit it off.

662
00:49:40,227 --> 00:49:43,063
You're both drifters

663
00:49:43,146 --> 00:49:46,233
who like to roam freely
without being tied down.

664
00:49:47,025 --> 00:49:48,151
You guys are alike.

665
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:51,279
Do you like him?

666
00:49:52,489 --> 00:49:53,657
No way!

667
00:49:53,740 --> 00:49:55,575
I have…

668
00:49:55,659 --> 00:49:59,496
Well, there was a man I almost married!

669
00:49:59,579 --> 00:50:00,580
That's too bad.

670
00:50:00,664 --> 00:50:04,584
I thought it'd be nice
to have you as my daughter-in-law.

671
00:50:05,460 --> 00:50:07,295
Well, I wouldn't mind

672
00:50:07,379 --> 00:50:10,507
having someone like you
as my father-in-law either.

673
00:50:10,590 --> 00:50:12,759
I like talking to you. It's fun.

674
00:50:13,260 --> 00:50:15,387
So, maybe we could be family someday.

675
00:50:15,470 --> 00:50:16,680
Absolutely not.

676
00:50:17,597 --> 00:50:20,392
You need to wash these, right?
I'll go do it.

677
00:50:21,893 --> 00:50:23,228
What's got into him?

678
00:50:29,693 --> 00:50:30,944
Damn.

679
00:50:35,073 --> 00:50:36,783
Is this thing broken or what?

680
00:50:42,831 --> 00:50:43,665
Screw this.

681
00:50:52,382 --> 00:50:55,677
I know I shouldn't be laughing,
but why is it so funny?

682
00:50:55,761 --> 00:50:57,262
Of course, it is.

683
00:50:57,345 --> 00:51:00,432
My analogy was spot-on. That's why.

684
00:51:10,233 --> 00:51:12,402
Oh my goodness. Look at me. I'm crying.

685
00:51:12,986 --> 00:51:15,614
Cry away, then. Just cry.

686
00:51:17,991 --> 00:51:19,493
Hey, you're back.

687
00:51:22,120 --> 00:51:23,955
Did you drop off the sample?

688
00:51:24,790 --> 00:51:25,874
Yes.

689
00:51:26,625 --> 00:51:27,709
Here, could you…?

690
00:51:27,793 --> 00:51:31,171
-For me?
-No, for my potential son.

691
00:51:32,089 --> 00:51:35,967
This is too awkward.
I'm going to go and pick some chilies.

692
00:51:37,928 --> 00:51:42,390
Try it. It's all organic.
He's been cooking for ages just for you.

693
00:51:43,767 --> 00:51:44,684
Careful. It's hot.

694
00:51:50,065 --> 00:51:50,899
Don't spill it.

695
00:52:02,327 --> 00:52:04,204
Occupational habit.

696
00:52:05,288 --> 00:52:09,084
I'm just so used
to wiping the kids' mouths

697
00:52:09,167 --> 00:52:11,378
because they spill food all the time.

698
00:52:15,966 --> 00:52:17,384
Let's have dinner.

699
00:52:25,976 --> 00:52:28,186
Better hurry now. Four minutes left.

700
00:52:28,270 --> 00:52:30,438
I can hear the train. Hurry up.

701
00:52:32,232 --> 00:52:35,277
Just pick up your damn phone,
you son of a bitch.

702
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:37,237
-Hello?
-<i>Hey, Kkari.</i>

703
00:52:37,320 --> 00:52:39,739
<i>-I've been meaning to call you.</i>
-Hello, sir.

704
00:52:39,823 --> 00:52:42,159
May I ask you something? I'm in a jam.

705
00:52:42,242 --> 00:52:45,245
Have you talked to Mr.,
I mean, that jerk, Hae Jo recently?

706
00:52:45,829 --> 00:52:48,123
<i>That's what I wanted to ask you about.</i>

707
00:52:48,206 --> 00:52:51,668
<i>I've been finding some addresses for him,</i>
<i>like he asked.</i>

708
00:52:51,751 --> 00:52:53,086
Sorry? Addresses?

709
00:52:53,587 --> 00:52:54,546
<i>What's going on?</i>

710
00:52:54,629 --> 00:52:57,048
<i>Don't get me involved in some fucked-up--</i>

711
00:52:57,132 --> 00:53:01,052
Can I have the addresses you gave him?

712
00:53:02,012 --> 00:53:04,389
Yes. You can text them to me. Thank you.

713
00:53:10,312 --> 00:53:12,022
What's this? You made our beds?

714
00:53:14,191 --> 00:53:17,194
It wasn't me.
Mr. Ko seems to think we're a couple.

715
00:53:17,694 --> 00:53:20,614
He's not being subtle about it.
Move farther back.

716
00:53:21,198 --> 00:53:22,616
Hey, don't be ungrateful.

717
00:53:24,784 --> 00:53:26,328
You two seem pretty close.

718
00:53:26,411 --> 00:53:27,704
Yes, it's strange.

719
00:53:28,205 --> 00:53:31,541
I've only just met him,
but I'm already opening up to him,

720
00:53:32,125 --> 00:53:33,168
just like that.

721
00:53:34,377 --> 00:53:36,171
I told him about my menopause.

722
00:53:36,922 --> 00:53:40,175
-What?
-That's why we were laughing earlier.

723
00:53:42,219 --> 00:53:45,513
<i>There was a potato</i>
<i>with a tiny baby potato attached to it.</i>

724
00:53:45,597 --> 00:53:46,932
<i>So I said</i>…

725
00:53:48,350 --> 00:53:51,269
Even potatoes have babies.
So what does that make me?

726
00:53:52,896 --> 00:53:54,689
A girl no better than a potato?

727
00:53:57,275 --> 00:53:59,027
And you know what he said?

728
00:53:59,945 --> 00:54:00,946
What did he say?

729
00:54:02,864 --> 00:54:04,866
<i>He grabbed the mushrooms and said,</i>

730
00:54:04,950 --> 00:54:09,454
<i>"Look, even mushrooms are marked</i>
<i>with the name of their producer."</i>

731
00:54:10,247 --> 00:54:13,375
"But Hae Jo
doesn't even know who made him!"

732
00:54:14,167 --> 00:54:16,169
<i>"So is he no better than a mushroom?"</i>

733
00:54:22,801 --> 00:54:23,927
My stomach hurts.

734
00:54:25,470 --> 00:54:28,056
I mean, it makes perfect sense,
doesn't it?

735
00:54:28,139 --> 00:54:30,267
How did he come up with that?

736
00:54:31,142 --> 00:54:32,560
It's just hilarious.

737
00:54:33,520 --> 00:54:34,437
You're right.

738
00:54:35,146 --> 00:54:38,525
I mean, it's really sad
if you think about it.

739
00:54:38,608 --> 00:54:41,319
But somehow, I find it hysterical.

740
00:54:45,031 --> 00:54:46,866
A girl no better than a potato.

741
00:54:47,742 --> 00:54:49,744
A guy no better than a mushroom.

742
00:54:53,248 --> 00:54:55,083
It's so funny.

743
00:55:05,176 --> 00:55:06,052
Jae-mi.

744
00:55:07,971 --> 00:55:08,805
Yes?

745
00:55:11,474 --> 00:55:12,517
You can just cry.

746
00:55:22,152 --> 00:55:23,862
Don't force yourself to laugh.

747
00:55:25,405 --> 00:55:26,823
Just cry instead.

748
00:55:37,208 --> 00:55:39,127
I'm tired. Switch off the lights.

749
00:56:45,110 --> 00:56:46,069
What is this?

750
00:56:48,321 --> 00:56:49,322
You know.

751
00:56:50,198 --> 00:56:52,200
Just a mushroom cuddling a potato.

752
00:59:46,833 --> 00:59:51,838
Subtitle translation by: Ahreum Woo
